loadBrainList           package:NeuroImage           R Documentation

_a _f_u_n_c_t_i_o_n _t_o _c_r_e_a_t_e _a "_B_r_a_i_n_L_i_s_t" _o_b_j_e_c_t _f_r_o_m _a _s_i_m_p_l_e _d_a_t_a._f_r_a_m_e _d_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_o_r

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     a convenience function to create a "BrainList" object from a text
     file description

_U_s_a_g_e:

     loadBrainList(tableSpec, path = NULL)

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

tableSpec: a two-column data.frame containing the labels and image file
          names 

    path: optional path to image files 

_D_e_t_a_i_l_s:

     the supplied data.frame must have two columns named "label" (for
     the image identifiers) and "file" for the image file names.  These
     are then used as key-value paris in the constructed 'BrainList'
     object. It is assumed that each opf the imege files are
     three-dimensional and this can be loaded with the 'loadVolume'
     function.

_V_a_l_u_e:

     an object of class 'BrainList'

